    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "ok so which side has more weight though? like if you're looking at the urgency of the climate crisis, is nuclear actually viable or is it just too risky?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Considering the urgency of the climate crisis, nuclear power's viability as a solution is a matter of intense debate and depends on individual assessment of the risks. Proponents argue that the industry must be more stringently regulated, with advanced safety measures in place, to mitigate the risks while harnessing nuclear energy's benefits for low-carbon electricity production. Critics hold that the risks are too high, especially with regard to accidents and waste management, and that investment should instead be directed to renewable sources and energy efficiency improvements that are inherently safer and sustainable. The consensus leans toward a balanced, diversified energy strategy that includes nuclear power among other solutions as part of a transition, rather than relying solely on nuclear power.",
